                  <persName id="t17770910-55-person463">
                  GEORGE
                   SPARLING
               <interp inst="t17770910-55-person463" type="surname" value="SPARLING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17770910-55-person463" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17770910-55-person463" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>The prisoner came into my shop to ask for a woman's coarse hat; I was at work, the hats lay by me on a joint stool; I said to her, you was here about a week ago, I told you then I kept no such hats; she said, you don't keep them ready-made; I said, no: as she was saying these words I saw her put her apron over the stool and take off the uppermost, which was a fine man's hat; I pursued her immediately, but she somehow got off; I went directly up Saffron-hill, and there I found her, but have not been able to discover my hat; I am positive the prisoner is the person that took the hat.</p>
               <p>The prisoner did not say any thing in her defence.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17770910-55-verdict270" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17770910-55-verdict270" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
